Author: <SHASHANK RAMGUDE>

PURPOSE:
    The purpose of this assignment is to create a generic library to serialize and deserialize objects, using dynamic proxy pattern.

FILES:
    1) driver/Driver.java
        This is responsible for:
        (1) Validating the command line arguments for input
            and output file names.
        (2) Calling proxy creator.
	(3) Calling writeObj or readObj methods according to the selected mode.

    2) server/SerStrategy.java - Interface for Serialziation strategy.

    3) server/DeserStrategy.java - Interface for Deserialziation strategy.

    4) server/StoreRestoreI.java - Tag interface.

    5) server/StoreI.java - Interface having writeObj methods.

    6) server/RestoreI.java - Interface having readObj methods.

    7) util/DeserializeTags.java - Class having method to deserialize tags.

    8) util/SerializeTags.java - Class having method to serialize tags.

    9) util/MyAllTypesFirst.java - Class having attributes.

    10) util/MyAllTypesSecond.java - Class having attributes.

    11) util/ProxyCreator.java - Class creating proxy.

    12) util/FileProcessor.java - Class having methods for file operation.

    13) util/SerializableObject.java - Empty base class.

    14) util/XMLSerialization.java - Class responsible for serializing objects.

    15) util/XMLDeserialization.java - Class responsible for deserializing objects.

    16) xmlStoreRestore/StoreRestoreHandler.java - Class having invoke method

JUSTIFICATION:
	Using strategy pattern gives flexibilty to add new startegies with minimal changes.


